Diageo Close to Buying Mey Icki of Turkey for Up to $2.5 Billion, WSJ Says

-- B y   C o r d e l l   E d d i n g s
-- 
2011-02-20T21:17:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-20/diageo-close-to-buying-mey-icki-of-turkey-for-up-to-2-5-billion-wsj-says.html
  Diageo Plc  is close to buying Mey
Icki Sanayi Ltd., a Turkish alcoholics-beverage company for as
much as $2.5 billion, The Wall Street Journal reported, citing
unidentified people familiar with the matter.  The purchase may be announced tomorrow, the newspaper said.
The Journal said that TPG Capital, which owns Mey Icki, had been
considering an initial public offering of the company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cordell Eddings in New York at 
 ceddings@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sylvia Wier at   swier@bloomberg.net  